00:08:12.792 --> 00:08:16.512
it may indicate that it has a non-pathogenic role given how prevalent it is,

141
00:08:16.952 --> 00:08:19.012
but at the very least, you can say we've got a lot of work to do.

142
00:08:20.692 --> 00:08:23.432
So depicted here, in this box and whisker plot,

143
00:08:24.492 --> 00:08:27.532
we've got blastocystis prevalence by age group.

144
00:08:27.692 --> 00:08:31.142
And you can see that blastocystis is prevalent among adults,

145
00:08:31.552 --> 00:08:34.852
maybe less so among children. And then not shown here is that it's nearly absent

146
00:08:36.112 --> 00:08:39.413
among infants and newborns. This really suggests to us that vertical

147
00:08:39.452 --> 00:08:42.972
transmission is not a mode of transmission for

148
00:08:43.033 --> 00:08:46.732
blastocystis. And then very interestingly, among the 12 publicly available

149
00:08:46.872 --> 00:08:48.472
data sets that we had that

150
00:08:49.392 --> 00:08:52.692
enrolled non-human primates, we saw a non-trivial

151
00:08:53.392 --> 00:08:56.892
prevalence of blastocystis, and almost all of these

152
00:08:56.952 --> 00:08:57.472
animals

153
00:08:58.872 --> 00:09:02.632
were held in captivity. And so this really suggested strongly to

154
00:09:02.752 --> 00:09:03.382
us that

155
00:09:04.212 --> 00:09:07.812
we may have stumbled upon a previously

156
00:09:07.852 --> 00:09:10.152
undescribed zoonotic transmission.

157
00:09:10.612 --> 00:09:14.382
So just some evidence that can be observed with

158
00:09:14.412 --> 00:09:17.621
digital sleuthing in population-scale microbiome studies.

159
00:09:19.612 --> 00:09:23.362
So depicted here in this line graph, we show that blastocystis carriage is linked

160
00:09:23.392 --> 00:09:25.292
to the consumption of healthy diets.

161
00:09:25.672 --> 00:09:26.192
Here,

162
00:09:27.192 --> 00:09:30.412
we can see that with greater adherence to a so-called plant-based diet,

163
00:09:31.612 --> 00:09:34.592
blastocystis prevalence increases monotonically.

164
00:09:35.202 --> 00:09:38.892
And then here is a slice of a much larger heat map, where we were able

165
00:09:38.952 --> 00:09:42.832
to demonstrate that here on the left, these are so-called putative good

166
00:09:42.892 --> 00:09:46.542
foods based on their loadings with that aforementioned plant-based diet, as well as

167
00:09:46.572 --> 00:09:50.512
their minimal level of processing, that with greater adherence to a

168
00:09:50.572 --> 00:09:53.612
healthier diet, blastocystis prevalence was greater.

169
00:09:54.072 --> 00:09:57.512
And then comparatively speaking, with a lower quality diet,

170
00:09:57.612 --> 00:09:59.872
blastocystis tended to be less prevalent.

171
00:10:03.092 --> 00:10:06.572
Here is where we performed a machine

172
00:10:06.652 --> 00:10:10.522
learner to demonstrate that blastocystis can be accurately predicted by

173
00:10:10.572 --> 00:10:14.232
bacterial gut composition, a previously undescribed trans-kingdom phenomenon,

174
00:10:15.092 --> 00:10:18.652
where we perform not only five-fold cross-validation but more robust

175
00:10:18.692 --> 00:10:21.592
sensitivity analysis using leave one data set out

176
00:10:23.192 --> 00:10:26.572
machine learning, where we can see that the median

177
00:10:26.652 --> 00:10:30.621
AUC is in the high 80s, demonstrating that gut

178
00:10:30.692 --> 00:10:33.812
bacterial composition can accurately predict the presence of

179
00:10:33.832 --> 00:10:34.732
blastocystis.

180
00:10:35.592 --> 00:10:39.442
And excitingly, we were able to demonstrate that among the features that

181
00:10:39.452 --> 00:10:41.341
were most important to this relationship

182
00:10:42.152 --> 00:10:44.652
was canonical diet-associated microbes like B.

183
00:10:44.712 --> 00:10:46.262
ovatus, and then

184
00:10:47.652 --> 00:10:50.672
negatively associated with blastocystis prevalence is oral

185
00:10:50.712 --> 00:10:51.652
pathobionts.

186
00:10:53.692 --> 00:10:57.672
And then here, limiting our data set to those from the ZOE PREDICT studies,

187
00:10:57.772 --> 00:11:01.592
we can see that blastocystis-positive participants generally had favorable

188
00:11:01.632 --> 00:11:05.452
cardiometabolic profiles, including improved fasting and

