higher so-called good cholesterol in HDL.

191
00:11:12.152 --> 00:11:15.912
They generally had improved responses to standardized test

192
00:11:15.952 --> 00:11:19.932
meals, as well as lower circulating levels of this inflammatory marker called

193
00:11:19.992 --> 00:11:20.432
GlicA.

194
00:11:22.852 --> 00:11:26.712
And then, similarly depicted in this line plot here is that

195
00:11:26.752 --> 00:11:28.312
blastocystis prevalence had

196
00:11:29.292 --> 00:11:33.092
decreased with greater adiposity, particularly among people

197
00:11:33.232 --> 00:11:34.552
who were overweight or obese.

198
00:11:35.792 --> 00:11:39.652
And here, among the publicly available data sets where we could calculate BMI,

199
00:11:40.232 --> 00:11:43.572
we found that for every one point increase in BMI, your odds of carrying

200
00:11:43.592 --> 00:11:45.532
blastocystis went down by 6%.

201
00:11:47.252 --> 00:11:50.422
Next, using a case control framework, which was defined at the study level,

202
00:11:51.352 --> 00:11:54.992
where controls were essentially the controls in a

203
00:11:55.012 --> 00:11:58.512
given individual study, and cases were

204
00:11:58.892 --> 00:12:02.572
diseases that are canonically known for maladapted host

205
00:12:02.652 --> 00:12:06.592
microbial interactions. We found a 29% decrease in the odds of harboring

206
00:12:06.652 --> 00:12:08.882
blastocystis among disease samples.

207
00:12:09.612 --> 00:12:13.502
In particular, this green dot here with colorectal cancer,

208
00:12:14.032 --> 00:12:18.012
as well as a pre-colorectal cancer

209
00:12:18.092 --> 00:12:19.792
condition called inflammatory bowel disease.

210
00:12:20.472 --> 00:12:21.612
We're currently following up on these

211
00:12:21.672 --> 00:12:25.528
leads.And next, in a randomized

212
00:12:25.548 --> 00:12:29.418
controlled trial of 1,100 individuals, we performed a personalized

213
00:12:29.448 --> 00:12:32.868
dietary intervention where blastocystis prevalence could

214
00:12:33.268 --> 00:12:37.228
expand modestly, particularly among people who were adhering

215
00:12:37.268 --> 00:12:38.508
to a higher quality diet,

216
00:12:39.408 --> 00:12:43.347
and especially people who met pre-specified weight loss goals.

217
00:12:44.128 --> 00:12:47.668
And we think that this may have implications for primary and secondary

218
00:12:47.728 --> 00:12:51.388
prevention of obesity-mediated cancers on the basis of

219
00:12:52.028 --> 00:12:54.048
data that we are still working on.

220
00:12:56.068 --> 00:12:59.428
So to wrap up this part of the talk, here in a global scale exploration,

221
00:13:00.108 --> 00:13:03.688
we show that human gut blastocystis has pretty distinct ethno-geographical

222
00:13:03.788 --> 00:13:07.028
patterning. It's positively associated with favorable short-term

223
00:13:07.108 --> 00:13:10.708
cardiometabolic markers and negatively associated with longer-term

224
00:13:10.788 --> 00:13:14.628
outcomes like body adiposity and especially colorectal cancer and other

225
00:13:14.668 --> 00:13:18.248
obesity-mediated cancers. Our findings suggest a

226
00:13:18.268 --> 00:13:22.088
potentially beneficial role for blastocystis, which may help explain personalized

227
00:13:22.108 --> 00:13:25.608
host responses to diet. And we have a little bit more

228
00:13:26.128 --> 00:13:29.788
mechanistic work that we're not quite prepared to show that hints at how this might

229
00:13:29.828 --> 00:13:31.008
be occurring. So stay tuned.

230
00:13:32.748 --> 00:13:36.188
The second part of my talk is on transkingdom dysbiosis in MASLD.

231
00:13:37.928 --> 00:13:41.388
MASLD stands for metabolic dysfunction-associated steatotic liver disease.

232
00:13:41.428 --> 00:13:43.528
It's a mouthful, so henceforth it'll be MASLD.

233
00:13:43.668 --> 00:13:47.328
It's a spectrum of disease where excess fat builds up in the liver.

234
00:13:47.468 --> 00:13:49.988
It's asymptomatic, but it is precancerous, as I mentioned.

235
00:13:50.388 --> 00:13:54.208
It's the most common liver disease in the Western

236
00:13:54.268 --> 00:13:58.108
Hemisphere and is slated to become the leading cause of liver cancer worldwide.

237
00:13:59.328 --> 00:14:02.748
As you might expect, it's associated with a variety of cardiometabolic

238
00:14:03.108 --> 00:14:06.948
disorders, including overweight or obesity, diabetes, and factors such as

239
00:14:06.988 --> 00:14:10.968
diet and smoking. Paradoxically, it can manifest in lean individuals.

240
00:14:14.288 --> 00:14:18.248
Most studies on the MASLD microbiome focus primarily on the bacterial fraction

241
00:14:18.268 --> 00:14:21.528
of the gut microbiome. So we elected not to focus on that.

242
00:14:21.648 --> 00:14:25.148
We jointly interrogated transkingdom components,

243
00:14:25.988 --> 00:14:29.648
taking a look at metagenomics, metatranscriptomics, as well as metabolomics.

244
00:14:30.328 --> 00:14:32.028
And forgive me for breezing through this slide.

